---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Getting Started — New Gen Agent"
  description="Step-by-step guide to install and run your first generative agent simulation."
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="wrap doc-content">
    <h1>Getting Started</h1>

    <section>
      <h2>Installation</h2>
      <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/DavideMeda/new-gen-agent.git
cd new-gen-agent
pip install -e ".[dev]"</code></pre>
      <p>Requires Python 3.10+. On Windows, use a virtual environment to avoid system conflicts.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Quick test (no LLM required)</h2>
      <pre><code>python examples/hello_world.py</code></pre>
      <p>
        Runs a 10-tick simulation with 3 agents (Alice, Bob, Carol) using a mock LLM.
        Completes in ~5 seconds. Output shows interactions and final stats.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>With Ollama (local LLM)</h2>
      <pre><code># 1. Install Ollama (https://ollama.ai)
ollama pull llama3.2:3b

# 2. Run simulation
python examples/ollama_simple.py</code></pre>
      <p>
        Uses <code>llama3.2:3b</code> for realistic agent dialogues. If Ollama is unavailable,
        the script auto-falls back to mock LLM and continues.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>With OpenRouter API (cloud LLM)</h2>
      <pre><code># 1. Get free API key from https://openrouter.ai
export OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...

# 2. Run simulation
python examples/openrouter_api.py</code></pre>
      <p>
        Supports 200+ models (free tier: meta-llama/llama-3.2-3b-instruct).
        Auto-fallback to mock if key is missing.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Cognitive biases demo</h2>
      <pre><code>python examples/cognitive_biases.py</code></pre>
      <p>
        Shows ConfirmationBias, AvailabilityHeuristic, and AnchoringBias in action.
        Uses mock LLM (no external dependencies).
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Custom scenario</h2>
      <p>See <code>examples/custom_scenario.py</code> for a commented template showing:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>How to define a custom world with POIs</li>
        <li>How to create agents with traits and initial memories</li>
        <li>How to configure <code>SimConfig</code> (tick interval, interaction radius, etc.)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Web UI (live dashboard)</h2>
      <pre><code>docker compose up</code></pre>
      <p>
        Starts FastAPI server on <code>http://localhost:8000</code> with WebSocket updates.
        Open the URL in a browser to see agents move, interact, and form memories in real time.
      </p>
      <p>For production (PostgreSQL + migrations), see <a href="https://github.com/DavideMeda/new-gen-agent/blob/main/docs/guides/DOCKER.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">docs/guides/DOCKER.md</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Running tests</h2>
      <pre><code>pytest                    # unit tests (fast, no LLM)
pytest tests/integration/ # requires server or Postgres</code></pre>
      <p>Coverage gate is 70%+. Pre-commit hooks run <code>ruff</code> and <code>mypy</code> automatically.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Next steps</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/DavideMeda/new-gen-agent/blob/main/docs/tutorials/GETTING_STARTED.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Full tutorial</a> — detailed walkthrough with troubleshooting</li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/DavideMeda/new-gen-agent/blob/main/docs/scenarios/SCENARIOS.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Scenarios guide</a> — built-in presets and how to create custom ones</li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/DavideMeda/new-gen-agent/blob/main/docs/research/LAYERS.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Research layers</a> — optional cognitive/social features</li>
        <li><a href="/docs">Advanced tutorials</a> — custom cognitive layers, LLM providers, production deployment</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .doc-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    padding: 4rem 1rem;
  }
  .doc-content h1 {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .doc-content section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  .doc-content h2 {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #00d9ff;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }
  .doc-content pre {
    background: #0f0f0f;
    border: 1px solid #222;
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }
  .doc-content code {
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  .doc-content p code {
    background: #1a1a1a;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }
  .doc-content ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
  .doc-content a {
    color: #00d9ff;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .doc-content a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
